- Anyone with repository access (employees, contractors, leaked repos) can see credentials
- Compiled/bundled JavaScript can be decompiled to extract strings
- Same credentials often reused across environments (dev/staging/prod)
- No ability to rotate credentials without code changes and redeployment
- Violates compliance requirements (PCI-DSS, SOC2, HIPAA)

